10640350@unknown@formal@none@1@S@== Features ==@1@3@@oe@30-11-2008
10640360@unknown@formal@none@1@S@According to its [[mission statement]], the OpenOffice.org project aims "''To create, as a community, the leading international office suite that will run on all major platforms and provide access to all functionality and data through open-component based APIs and an XML-based file format.''"@1@43@@oe@30-11-2008
10640370@unknown@formal@none@1@S@OpenOffice.org aims to compete with Microsoft Office and emulate its look and feel where suitable.@1@15@@oe@30-11-2008
10640380@unknown@formal@none@1@S@It can read and write most of the [[file formats]] found in Microsoft Office, and many other applications; an essential feature of the suite for many users.@1@27@@oe@30-11-2008
10640390@unknown@formal@none@1@S@OpenOffice.org has been found to be able to open files of older versions of Microsoft Office and damaged files that newer versions of Microsoft Office itself cannot open.@1@28@@oe@30-11-2008
10640400@unknown@formal@none@1@S@However, it cannot open older Word for Macintosh (MCW) files.@1@10@@oe@30-11-2008
