10640920@unknown@formal@none@1@S@== Development ==@1@3@@oe@30-11-2008
10640930@unknown@formal@none@1@S@=== Overview ===@1@3@@oe@30-11-2008
10640940@unknown@formal@none@1@S@The OpenOffice.org [[Application Programming Interface|API]] is based on a component technology known as [[Universal Network Objects]] (UNO).@1@17@@oe@30-11-2008
10640950@unknown@formal@none@1@S@It consists of a wide range of interfaces defined in a [[CORBA]]-like [[interface description language]].@1@15@@oe@30-11-2008
10640960@unknown@formal@none@1@S@The [[document file format]] used is based on [[XML]] and several export and import filters.@1@15@@oe@30-11-2008
10640970@unknown@formal@none@1@S@All external formats read by OpenOffice.org are converted back and forth from an internal XML representation.@1@16@@oe@30-11-2008
10640980@unknown@formal@none@1@S@By using [[data compression|compression]] when saving [[XML]] to disk, files are generally smaller than the equivalent binary Microsoft Office documents.@1@20@@oe@30-11-2008
10640990@unknown@formal@none@1@S@The native file format for storing documents in version 1.0 was used as the basis of the [[OASIS (organization)|OASIS]] OpenDocument file format standard, which has become the default file format in version 2.0.@1@33@@oe@30-11-2008
10641000@unknown@formal@none@1@S@Development versions of the suite are released every few weeks on the developer zone of the OpenOffice.org website.@1@18@@oe@30-11-2008
10641010@unknown@formal@none@1@S@The releases are meant for those who wish to test new features or are simply curious about forthcoming changes; they are not suitable for production use.@1@26@@oe@30-11-2008
